    "description": "Shima Seiki Mfg.,Ltd., together with its subsidiaries, develops, manufactures, sells, markets, and services knitting machines, design systems, and automatic fabric cutting machines in Japan, Europe, the Middle East, rest of Asia, and internationally. The company offers computerized flat, and glove and sock knitting machines under the WHOLEGARMENT brand; and peripherals. It also provides SDS-ONE APEX series, which consists of an all-in-one system, a design system with integrated hardware and software; and APEXFiz, a design software subscription service. In addition, the company offers P-CAM, a series of automatic fabric cutting machines; P-LAB automatic labeling machines; P-SPR 2 spreading machines; PMK 1600/2000 inkjet marking plotters; CAD/CAM systems; and SHIMA KnitManager, a production management software. Further, it is involved in the provision of service and maintenance services; manufacture of machine parts; production of cashmere yarns; sale of REPAC and ReMateri yarns; operation of BLUEKNIT, an online shopping mall for knits; Auberge de South Terrace, a hotel located in Nanki Shirahama; food services business; and museum. The company serves the fashion, sports/outdoor, healthcare, shoes and accessories, home furnishings, automotive, aeronautical, and industrial materials industries. It exports its products. Shima Seiki Mfg.,Ltd. was founded in 1961 and is headquartered in Wakayama, Japan."
